    <title>Medicare Home Health Flexibility Act of 2015</title>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Medicare Home Health Flexibility Act of 2015</strong></p> <p>This bill&nbsp;establishes circumstances under which an&nbsp;occupational therapist&nbsp;may conduct the initial assessment visit for an individual who is eligible for home health services under Medicare. Specifically, an occupational therapist may conduct the assessment if the physician's referral order does not include skilled nursing care but does include: (1) occupational therapy, and (2) physical therapy or speech language pathology.</p>]]></text>
